speaker: Apiza
text: To connect to a particular host, you may use ssh_options_set(ssh_session session, enum ssh_options_e type, const void * value ) using the parameter SSH_OPTIONS_HOST: The hostname or ip address to connect to (const char *).

speaker: Apiza
text: For example: ssh_options_set(my_session, SSH_OPTIONS_HOST, "localhost");

speaker: Programmer
text: What does ssh_connect return?

speaker: Apiza
text: Returns SSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR on error. SSH_AGAIN, if the session is in nonblocking mode, and call must be done again.

text: What does ssh_is_server_known return in libssh?

speaker: Programmer
text: What does ssh_disconnect return in libssh

speaker: Programmer
text: What does ssh_free return in libssh?

speaker: Apiza
text:
ssh_is_server_known returns SSH_SERVER_KNOWN_OK: The server is known and has not changed.
SSH_SERVER_KNOWN_CHANGED: The server key has changed. Either you are under attack or the administrator changed the key. You HAVE to warn the user about a possible attack.
SSH_SERVER_FOUND_OTHER: The server gave use a key of a type while we had an other type recorded. It is a possible attack.
SSH_SERVER_NOT_KNOWN: The server is unknown. User should confirm the MD5 is correct.
SSH_SERVER_FILE_NOT_FOUND: The known host file does not exist. The host is thus unknown. File will be created if host key is accepted.
SSH_SERVER_ERROR: Some error happened.

speaker: Apiza
text: ssh_disconnect returns void.

text: ssh_free returns void.

speaker: Apiza
text: ssh_channel_request_exec(ssh_channel channel, const char * cmd).

speaker: Apiza
text: Parameters are 1) channel: The channel to execute the command. 2) cmd: The command to execute (e.g. "ls ~/ -al | grep -i reports").

speaker: Apiza
text: ssh_channel_request_exec returns SSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.

text: You may be looking for ssh_channel_read(ssh_channel channel, void * dest, uint32_t count, int is_stderr ).

speaker: Apiza
